inn1.comm: half volley on the off, drives firmly, great fielding by a diving Dabengwa
off cutter is left alone, ooohhhs, from behind the wicket
fuller ball on the leg, looks to flick fine, gets the leading edge to mid-on, good diving catch to rainsford's right
line and length, maybe just a touch straight, defends back to the bolwer

great ball, draws the batsman onto the front foot, cuts away off the pitch, well bea
ten

defends firmly down the pitch, Iqbal trying to get back to the crease gets the bat 
in the way, well fielded by the batsman
thick edge down to third man, easy single

inn2.comm: half volley is dispatched straight down the ground
leg side, appeals for the leg before down the leg side, but that was very optimistic
well flighted, stroked down the pitch, bowler gets across and gets a foot to it
well forward, soft hands to cover point, fielder caught on the heels
Another change as Ruben starts outside off, short, cuts hard, beaten, Price not happy with himself
beaten by a bit of pace as he fires that in short of length, just outside off, too close to cut, beaten
good length and line, Price tries to swing that across the line, bit late, dargs that with no timing to mid-on
gets a very good leg stump yorker, dug out, bit across the line, keeps it out to the on side
excellent ball, on line and length, no other choice but to defend down the pitch
well forward again looks to work it on side, inside edge squirts to square leg
starts with an attempted yorker, too full, clips to the on side for an easy run
gets well forward, strokes the drive towards long on
worked from he front foot towards the deep square leg
all defensive, stroked bac at the bowler
line and length, gets well forward with another solid looking defence
just outside off, nudges towards backward point, a slight hesitation, confusion, throw is wide and the 100 comes up
full on the off, firmly drives, not timed towards mid-off
oh dear goes leg side, attempted flick, beats the bat, not the pad, beats a diving keeper, huge release for Zimbabwe
back on line and length, Mupariwa showing a lot of experience here, defends to the off
leg side again, flicks, gets bat on that straight at short fine leg, quick run, lucky that the throw was wide
short on the off, gets back and gently steers that to third man
all defensive to a good delivery, right on target and well kept out
oh dear, pressure seems to be shifting to Bangladesh, wide fired in down the leg side
leg side again, beats the bat but not the pad, runs wide of short fine leg
good looking drive into the cover area, good scrambled bit of fielding saves three runs
leg side again, worked off the legs off the back foot, easy run taken
flighted on the off, goes over the top, clears the inner ring at mid-off, races back dives and saves the boundary
short, almost a long hop, punched down the ground towards long on
flighted on the off, drives firmly towards mid-off, does not beat him
Oh, pressure on Shakib as well, fires one in well wide down the leg side
All defensive from Price, gets well forward and smothers
Once again he is well forward all defensive, looks like he wants to play this ast over out
Get well forward to this one, was in line till it gripped and turned away beating the outside edge, very close
Almost on the front foot as Shakib bowls, gets one that turns and bounces, but using the outside half of the bat he keeps that out
gets a big stride in to cover the turn and bounce, defends to the bowler
a good over from Shakib, apart from the wide, brings an end to his 10 over spell, 3/11, thats some bowling
gets on the back foot to a shortish ball, punched wide of point who dives across gathers on his hands and knees
full on the off, stroked to the off, wide of mid-off who gets across but cant save the single
leg side, touch short, worked off the hips to the on side, target getting closer
wicket is now needed as Prices dabs towards mid-on, quick run taken, throw is wide, but replay shows him home anyway
short, bouncer, slashes a cut at it, but that was high, keeper takes, gives the bowler a clap, but lucky to get away with theheight on that ball
another short one, this one does not get up but the batsman is ducking anyway, another valuable dot
Shuffles down the pitch, swings that fullish ball across the line, beating a diving midwicket, and swings the game back towards Zimbabwe
touch short on the legs, gets inside that delivery, flicks it off his hips and whips it away to deep backward square leg
